Used to be a time in highschool I watched a lot of Serbian war footage. Something that hit me was a random video of military unit moving with a Bosniak village in the background, one large brick house burning, entire thing in flames, no one paying attention. House looked good

Was obvious a family lived there until recently. They probably followed the war news on the TV, in the newspapers, it seemed unreal to them, it was impossible to come into reality, but it did, and they had to flee and have their home destroyed in fire.

Evola said in our age power does not care, you can no longer ignore power as in the deep past, you can pretend it does not matter, that reality does not affect you, but eventually power will force you to submit to it, it will invade your world
